                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="evaluation" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Software Evaluation Checklist</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70 mb-4">Use this checklist when evaluating any HVAC software platform:</p>
              <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
                <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Free trial or live demo available?</strong> Never buy software you have not tested.</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Published pricing?</strong> If they hide pricing, expect aggressive sales tactics.</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>QuickBooks integration?</strong> Must be native two-way sync, not just Zapier.</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Mobile app ratings?</strong> Check App Store and Google Play reviews from the last 6 months.</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Contract terms?</strong> Prefer month-to-month. If annual, negotiate a discount.</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Data export?</strong> Can you export all your customer and job data if you leave?</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Support quality?</strong> Call their support line before buying. How long is the wait?</span></div>
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-primary font-mono text-xs mt-0.5">□</span> <span><strong>Implementation support?</strong> Do they help with data migration and onboarding?</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="mistakes" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">5 Common Software Mistakes HVAC Companies Make</h2>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="border-l-2 border-red-400 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-1">1. Buying too much software too early</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">A solo operator does not need ServiceTitan, call tracking, and review management. Start with a basic CRM and QuickBooks. Add tools as your revenue and complexity grow.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-2 border-red-400 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-1">2. Choosing based on features instead of fit</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">The platform with the most features is not always the best choice. A tool your team actually uses beats a powerful tool they avoid because it is too complex.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-2 border-red-400 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-1">3. Ignoring the true cost</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">The sticker price is never the full cost. Factor in add-ons, per-user fees, implementation costs, and the tools you will need to supplement gaps in the platform.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-2 border-red-400 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-1">4. Not testing with your actual team</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">The owner might love a platform, but if your dispatcher and technicians find it confusing, adoption will fail. Include your team in the evaluation process.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border-l-2 border-red-400 pl-4">
                  <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm mb-1">5. Signing long-term contracts without testing</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">Never sign an annual contract without at least 2 weeks of hands-on testing. If a vendor will not offer a trial, that is a red flag.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

